[resource]
script = ExtResource("3_x6aa3")
id = "create_external_resource"
title = "Create external resource"
description = "**Purpose**
Create a new resource file (.tres) based on a specified class. This is useful when a resource needs to be reused.

**Usage notes**
- The `file_path` parameter specifies where the resource will be created.
- The `base_class` parameter determines the type of the resource.
- The file must not exist at the specified path.
- The resource will be created with default properties.
- Missing directories in the `file_path` will be created.

**Example**
file_path: res://resources/enemy_area.tres
base_class: RectnagleShape2D"
category = ExtResource("1_f3tws")
parameters = Array[ExtResource("2_2mou1")]([SubResource("Resource_edr3s"), SubResource("Resource_r2kgk"), ExtResource("7_e7oa3")])
options = Array[ExtResource("1_rnfby")]([ExtResource("3_4x5xo"), ExtResource("4_1r5p2"), ExtResource("5_pxdw5")])
